description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCFT&#39;s Estates operational department provides a wide range of Estates operational maintenance services throughout the Trust&#39;s community settings across Sussex. The Estates department provides and receives services to its own Trust and to neighbouring Trusts via service level agreements (SLAs).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a proactive team player who is willing to work flexibly and be part of a dynamic workforce, meeting the challenges of a forward-thinking organisation that has been rated “Good” and “Outstanding” by the Care Quality Commission (CQC).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the Support Services Officer, the post holder will work alongside the Trust’s Electro-Medical Engineering Manager (EME) and will be responsible for the database systems that support the Estates and EME services, providing management support of the in-house helpdesk and EME Technicians, and assisting the EME Manager with external SLAs and contracts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will assist in analysing performance of the overall service in relation to Estates and EME. This role will be accountable to the Electro-Medical Engineering Manager and will provide IT technical support to a team of highly technical staff to provide an efficient, reliable, planned and reactive maintenance service. They&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; will collaborate with various staff members in order to support the Estates service within the Trust, and assist in service improvement and asset tracking systems for a Trust-wide Medical Device service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will need good analytical and problem solving skills, and the ability to work well under pressure to achieve results for the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stephen Sinclair&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Electro-Medical Engineering Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;stephen.sinclair5@nsh.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01273 696011 ext. 4116&lt;/p&gt;
